  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison is replying to a letter from Richard Davis Webb regarding Mary Anne Estlin&apos;s comments about George Thompson. Garrison writes: &quot;No person better knows the infirmities of G.T. than I do; and he has never found me backward in giving both expostulation and advice.&quot; George Thompson&apos;s temperament and financial difficulties are described. Mary Estlin seems to have objected to the proposal that George Thompson lecture in Great Britain on behalf of the freedmen&apos;s cause. George Thompson&apos;s poor health is described.</subfield>
  </datafield>
